name: frontside
description: Both feet in the groove with your body facing towards the obstacle.

name: backside
description: Both feet in the groove with your body facing away from the obstacle.

name: ufo
description: Both feet in the groove - the same as a frontside. The difference is to bend your ankles and knees outwards and get super low.

name: cabdriver
description: Both feet in the groove but with your skates angled inwards at around a 45 degree angle.

name: royale
description: Both feet in the groove with your skates and wheels angled towards the grinding direction. You'll need to bend your knees and get a little low.

name: unity
description: Crossed legged grind with both feet in the groove. The front foot wraps over the back foot.

name: savannah
description: Crossed legged grind with both feet in the groove. The front foot wraps behind the back foot.

name: farv
description: Both feet in the groove with your skates and wheels angled away from the grinding direction. You'll need to bend your knees and get low.

name: torque
description: A one footed grind with your leading foot in the groove with your skate and wheels angled away from the grinding direction.

name: backslide
description: A one footed grind with your leading foot in the groove with your skate and wheels angled towards the grinding direction.

name: fastslide
description: A one footed grind with your leading foot in the groove so that the soul plate faces the grinding direction. Your skate shouldn't be angled in the groove, avoiding any contact with the soul plate.

name: pudslide
description: A one footed grind with your leading foot in the groove so that the negative plate faces the grinding direction. Your skate shouldn't be angled in the groove, avoiding any contact with the soul plate.

name: tabernacle
description: Both feet in the groove, front foot turned outwards in a backslide position, back foot behind like a mizou.

name: wheelbarrow
description: Leading foot rolls on the heel or toe on the obstacle  while the back foot grinds in groove.

name: byn soul
description: Both feet in the groove, front foot turned inward towards the obstacle like a normal soul but your back foot should be in the torque position.
